## Block certificate

> Headers

```
Content-type: application/json
```

> Body example

```json
{
    "shop_id": "...",
    "shop_secret": "...",
    "code": "..."
}
```

> Request example

```shell
curl --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
  --request PATCH \
  --data-binary "@data.json" \
  https://<%= config[:api_endpoint] %>/loyalty/certificates/block
```

> The above command returns JSON structured like this:

```json
{
  "status": "success"
}
```

Temporarily blocks a certificate. Blocked certificate can be unblocked.

### HTTP Request

`PATCH https://<%= config[:api_endpoint] %>/loyalty/certificates/block`
### Query Parameters

| Parameter   | Required | Description                                                         |
|-------------|----------|---------------------------------------------------------------------|
| shop_id     | true     | Your API key                                                        |
| shop_secret | true     | Your API secret key                                                 |
| code        | true     | Certificate code                                                    |




